OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fafter unwanted office      
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fbirthday party             
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, A Kentucky man has been awarded        
OL,6, $450,000 (#345,314) after his company  
OL,7, threw him a surprise birthday party    
OL,8, despite his warnings that it would     
OL,9, trigger stress and anxiety.            
OL,11,FThe plaintiff, Kevin Berling, claims   
OL,12,Fthat the unwanted 2019 birthday party  
OL,13,Fat Gravity Diagnostics caused him a    
OL,14,Fseries of panic attacks.               
OL,16,FMr Berling's lawsuit alleged that the  
OL,17,Fcompany discriminated against him based
OL,18,Fon a disability.                       
OL,20,FThe company has denied any wrongdoing. 
